#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1671
#, no-c-format
msgid "This option affects the current state of the domain. If the domain is inactive, the device is added to the persistent XML and will be available on next boot. If the domain is active, the device is hotplugged but not added to the persistent XML."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1680
#, no-c-format
msgid "To detach a VF interface, use the <command>virsh detach-device</command> command, which also takes the options listed above."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1690
#, no-c-format
msgid "Dynamic Allocation of VFs from a Pool"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1691
#, no-c-format
msgid "If you define the PCI address of a VF into a guest's configuration statically as described in <xref linkend=\"sec.libvirt.config.io.attach\"/> , it is hard to migrate such guest to another host. The host must have identical hardware in the same location on the PCI bus, or the guest configuration must be modified prior to each start."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1699
#, no-c-format
msgid "Another approach is to create a &libvirt; network with a device pool that contains all the VFs of an <xref linkend=\"vt.io.sriov\"/> device. The guest then references this network, and each time it is started, a single VF is dynamically allocated to it. When the guest is stopped, the VF is returned to the pool, available for another guest."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1707
#, no-c-format
msgid "Defining Network with Pool of VFs on &vmhost;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1708
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following example of network definition creates a pool of all VFs for the <xref linkend=\"vt.io.sriov\"/> device with its physical function (PF) at the network interface eth0 on the host:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1713
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;network&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;name&gt;passthrough&lt;/name&gt;\n"
      "    &lt;forward mode='hostdev' managed='yes'&gt;\n"
      "      &lt;pf dev='eth0'/&gt;\n"
      "    &lt;/forward&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;/network&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1719
#, no-c-format
msgid "To use this network on the host, save the above code to a file, for example <filename>/tmp/passthrough.xml</filename> , and execute the following commands. Remember to replace eth0 with the real network interface name of your <xref linkend=\"vt.io.sriov\"/> device's PF:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1725
#, no-c-format
msgid "&prompt.user;virsh net-define /tmp/passthrough.xml\n"
      "&prompt.user;virsh net-autostart passthrough\n"
      "&prompt.user;virsh net-start passthrough"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: title
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1730
#, no-c-format
msgid "Configuring &vmguest; to Use VF from the Pool"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1731
#, no-c-format
msgid "The following example of guest device interface definition uses a VF of the <xref linkend=\"vt.io.sriov\"/> device from the pool created in <xref linkend=\"libvirt.config.io.pool.host\"/> . &libvirt; automatically derives the list of all VFs associated with that PF the first time the guest is started."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1738
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;interface type='network'&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;source network='passthrough'&gt;\n"
      "&lt;/interface&gt;"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1741
#, no-c-format
msgid "To verify the list of associated VFs, run <command>virsh net-dumpxml passthrough</command> on the host after the first guest that uses the network with the pool of VFs starts."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: screen
#: libvirt_configuration.xml:1746
#, no-c-format
msgid "&lt;network connections='1'&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;name&gt;passthrough&lt;/name&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;uuid&gt;a6a26429-d483-d4ed-3465-4436ac786437&lt;/uuid&gt;\n"
      "  &lt;forward mode='hostdev' managed='yes'&gt;\n"
      "    &lt;pf dev='eth0'/&gt;\n"
